// PLACEHOLDER — upstream graphify MCP server is not yet released
// (see https://github.com/safishamsi/graphify/issues/146).
//
// When the upstream MCP module ships, this is the launcher pattern that
// will work: `--from graphifyy` (correct PyPI package name, with double-y)
// and `--with mcp` because graphifyy does NOT pull the `mcp` package into
// its dependencies (upstream gap, see SETUP_GUIDE.md "Why --with mcp").
//
// Prerequisites once the MCP server exists:
//   1. `uv tool install graphifyy`
//   2. `graphify .` — produces `graphify-out/graph.json` (server needs it)
//   3. uncomment / merge this block into your project's `.mcp.json` under
//      `"mcpServers"` (strip the JS comments — JSON doesn't allow them)
//
// Until then: use the CLI (`graphify .`) and the `/graphify` skill, which
// read `graphify-out/graph.json` directly without an MCP server.
{
  "graphify": {
    "command": "uv",
    "args": [
      "tool",
      "run",
      "--from",
      "graphifyy",
      "--with",
      "mcp",
      "python",
      "-m",
      "graphify.serve",
      "graphify-out/graph.json"
    ]
  }
}
